Description: Papyrus; twenty-three fragments; Hieratic text recto and verso.
Curator's comments: Photographs given to N. Baum for study (by S. Quirke?): to be published by her and F. Herbin (confirmed Feb. 2020). M. Gabolde comments on: une liste de 13 vases consignée sur le fragment C, col. III, l. 11 du papyrus BM 10795 (J. Cerny, Coptic etymological Dictionary, p. 88). Je remercie les autorités du BM, et spécialement >> R. Parkinson d'avoir bien voulu m'autoriser à citer cet onomasticon. La transcription hiéroglyphique de ce texte par J. Cerny = le manuscrit de ce chercheur 8.53-4 (Griffith Institute). It complements the Onomastica published by Gardiner. Frg. B is paralleled with AEO pl. XI, l. 1-2 and starts with a strange new mention of the city of Djarukha with an unexpected orthography.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (57275) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/57275)
